title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Generate a Wayang plan that computes, for each nation and each year, the total profit for all parts whose name contains the substring ‘green’. Profit is defined as (l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount)) - (ps_supplycost * l_quantity). Join the part, supplier, lineitem, partsupp, orders, and nation tables through their keys. Extract the order year, filter parts so that p_name contains ‘green’, and group the results by nation and year. Output in a textfile.

operations.udf: (t: (((Int, Int), (Int, Double, Double, Double)), ((Int, Int), Double))) => { val leftKey = t._1._1; val leftVal = t._1._2; val supplycost = t._2._2; val suppkey = leftKey._2; val orderkey = leftVal._1; val extended = leftVal._2; val discount = leftVal._3; val quantity = leftVal._4; (suppkey, (orderkey, extended, discount, quantity, supplycost)) }

(t: ((Int, (Int, Double, Double, Double, Double)), (Int, Int))) => { val suppkey = t._1._1; val rec = t._1._2; val orderkey = rec._1; val extended = rec._2; val discount = rec._3; val quantity = rec._4; val supplycost = rec._5; val nationkey = t._2._2; (orderkey, (nationkey, extended, discount, quantity, supplycost)) }

(t: ((Int, (Int, Double, Double, Double, Double)), (Int, Int))) => { val orderRec = t._2; val orderkey = orderRec._1; val year = orderRec._2; val nationkey = t._1._2._1; val extended = t._1._2._2; val discount = t._1._2._3; val quantity = t._1._2._4; val supplycost = t._1._2._5; ((nationkey, year), (extended, discount, quantity, supplycost)) }

(t: (( (Int, Int), (Double, Double, Double, Double) ), (Int, String))) => { val key = t._1._1; val nationname = t._2._2; val year = key._2; val extended = t._1._2._1; val discount = t._1._2._2; val quantity = t._1._2._3; val supplycost = t._1._2._4; val profit = (extended * (1.0 - discount)) - (supplycost * quantity); ((nationname, year), profit) }
(a: ((String, Int), Double), b: ((String, Int), Double)) => (a._1, a._2 + b._2)

log.thoughts: Filtered parts by name containing 'green', joined tables to bring supply cost, supplier and nation, extracted order year, computed profit per line and aggregated by (nation, year), then wrote results to a text file.
